reviewText: I found this movie by accident while surfing the channels one day.  I decided to buy it for my collection.  I love Shelly Winters and her body of work.  Ricardo Montalban portrayed a side of his acting ability I had never seen.  Previously, I only knew of him in in television roles.  Wendell Corey and Claire Trevor give a good performance.  You can feel each actor's role- Montalban uplifting, Corey racism, Trevor beat down and angry, and Winters beaten by life, but heroic.
Solid performances, interesting characters, enjoyable journey not seldom taken.  Good movie.
